
Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I go to Page 05 of Elbow MRI

When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled
When I select 'Osteochondral lesion' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled

And 'Anterior humeral capitulum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Posterior humeral capitulum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Anterior humeral trochlea' checkbox is enabled
And 'Posterior humeral trochlea' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ulna, trochlear notch' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ulna, radial notch' checkbox is enabled
And 'Radius, fovea capitis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Radius, circumferentia radii' checkbox is enabled

And 'Size' input field is enabled
And '2nd plane' input field is enabled
And '3rd plane' input field is enabled

And 'Open physis' radio button is enabled
And 'Closed physis' radio button is enabled

And 'Joint effusion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hemarthros' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Anterior humeral capitulum' checkbox
Or I select 'Posterior humeral capitulum' checkbox
Then 'General' radio button is enabled
And 'Itsubo Classification' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Anterior humeral capitulum' checkbox
And I select 'Posterior humeral capitulum' checkbox
Then 'General' radio button is enabled
And 'Itsubo Classification' radio button is enabled

When I select 'General' radio button
Then 'Cartilage intact, stable lesion' radio button is enabled
And 'Chondral lesion, unstable lesion' radio button is enabled
And 'Organized defect, completely filled with fluid' radio button is enabled
